8 POLICY COMMITTEE RECOMMENDATION
9 An Act relating to the Oklahoma Child Care Facilities
Licensing Act; requiring one master teacher for
10 certain number of enrolled children; providing for
codification; and declaring an emergency.
11
12
13
14 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
15 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
16 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 404.4 of Title 10, unless there
17 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
18 The master teacher ratio required for two-, three-, four- and
19 five-star centers shall be one (1) full-time master teacher for
20 every sixty (60) children actually enrolled at a licensed child care
21 facility.
22 SECTION 2. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
23 of the public peace, health or safety, an emergency is hereby
24
